  <h2>HTML TAGS</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Tag</th>
        <th>Specific Name</th>
        <th>Description</th>
        <th>Use On</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <!-- use (&lt;) to represent <  and (&gt;) to represent > --> 
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>&lt;Div&gt;</td>
        <td>Division</td>
        <td>Div acts as a container for elements</td>
        <td>We use it for grouping elements in HTML</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>&lt;p&gt;</td>
        <td>Paragraph</td>
        <td>Paragraph for large amounts of text</td>
        <td>When we want to write a lot for a Specific text or image</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>&lt;br&gt;</td>
        <td>Line Break</td>
        <td>Line break on HTML code for some distance</td>
        <td>We use it when we want to see it on Browser</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>&lt;ul&gt;</td>
        <td>Unordered Lists</td>
        <td>Makes boolians on our on list we use it on</td>
        <td>We use it with &lt;li&gt; element so we make lists with boolians</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>&lt;ol&gt;</td>
        <td>Ordered Lists</td>
        <td>Makes the list with numbers</td>
        <td>We use it with &lt;li&gt; element so we make lists with numeric values</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>&lt;img&gt;</td>
        <td>Image</td>
        <td>Image is a self closing tag with means it doesnt require to have a closing tag</td>
        <td>We use it for images</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>&lt;video&gt;</td>
        <td>Video</td>
        <td>Places a video on the website requires a closing tag</td>
        <td>If we want to have video on our website</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>&lt;audio&gt;</td>
        <td>Audio</td>
        <td>Places a audio file in the website requires a closing tag</td>
        <td>We use it on our website for audio files</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>&lt;html&gt;</td>
        <td>HTML5</td>
        <td>All between the opening and closing html tags will be proceeded as HTML code</td>
        <td>We use it after !DOCTYPE declaration for our website to work</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>&lt;head&gt;</td>
        <td>Head</td>
        <td>The head element has the metadata of a webpage(metadata is the informations about he website itself)</td>
        <td>We use it to place metadata such as the tittle of a webpage, Links for CSS e.t.c.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>&lt;body&gt;</td>
        <td>Body</td>
        <td>Body tag is where the code is nested. This is where we write code that saw in a webpage</td>
        <td>We use it after the head tag and we place our code there</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>&lt;title&gt;</td>
        <td>Title</td>
        <td>This is the title of a website</td>
        <td>We use it for the title to show on the website</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>&lt;a&gt;</td>
        <td>Anchor</td>
        <td>We connect pages or links on our own website</td>
        <td>We use it for links on our pages</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>&lt;span&gt;</td>
        <td>Span</td>
        <td>Is an inline element that is usually wrapped inside another element.</td>
        <td>Is used for grouping text or elements together for styling and scripting.</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <h2>Attributes</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Attribute</th>
        <th>Specific Name</th>
        <th>Description</th>
        <th>Use On</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>alt</td>
        <td>Alternative</td>
        <td>Is an alternative text used by screen readers and when the image does not load.</td>
        <td>We use it inside the image tag if the image failts to load</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>href</td>
        <td>Hyperlink Reference</td>
        <td>The path or address required to connect a path</td>
        <td>We use it usually with an anchor element to show the path we use</td>     
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <h2>HTML Tables</h2>
  <p>Table elements are for creating panels to show better data</p>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Table</th>
        <th>Name</th>
        <th>Description</th>
        <th>Use On</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>&lt;table&gt;</td>
        <td>Table</td>
        <td>The table contains all the tabular data we want to show</td>
        <td>We use it for tabular data</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>&lt;tr&gt;</td>
        <td>Table Rows</td>
        <td>Places a row in the table element for us to place data</td>
        <td>We use it for rows in a table</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>&lt;td&gt;</td>
        <td>Table Data</td>
        <td>Rows are not enough for adding data so we use the table data</td>
        <td>We use it after a table row for adding data</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>&lt;th&gt;</td>
        <td>Table Headings</td>
        <td>Adds titles for our table rows and table datas</td>
        <td>We use it for titles</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>colspan</td>
        <td>Spanning Columns</td>
        <td>Data that they stretch require the colspan attribute</td>
        <td>We use it for stretching columns</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>rowspan</td>
        <td>Spanning Rows</td>
        <td>Data can also span multiple rows this is an attribute</td>
        <td>We use it for spanning rows in a table</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>&lt;tbody&gt;</td>
        <td>Table Body</td>
        <td>We separate the table so we keep better track</td>
        <td>We use it so we can exclude the table only for data(this cant contain the table heading)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>&lt;thead&gt;</td>
        <td>Table Head</td>
        <td>The heading for a table are nested inside</td>
        <td>We use it for headings</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>&lt;tfooter&gt;</td>
        <td>Table Footer</td>
        <td colspan="2">The last part of a table usually used for adding elements</td>
      </tr>
      
    </tbody>
